Ayala Land, Metro, SM Development: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-02-14T00:37:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/ayala-land-metro-sm-development-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of noon in Manila on Feb. 11.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.3 percent to
3,749.15, halting a three-day drop.    Ayala Land Inc . (ALI PM): The Southeast Asian nation’s
largest builder said capital spending will rise to 32.6 billion
pesos ($744 million) this year from 20.1 billion pesos in 2010
to fund ongoing and new projects and to expand its  land bank .  Profit in 2010 rose 35 percent to a record 5.46 billion
pesos as revenue climbed 24 percent,  Ayala Land  said in a filing
to the Philippine Stock Exchange. The stock rose 1.5 percent to
14 pesos.    Metro Pacific Investments Corp . (MPI PM): The investment
holding company was rated “hold” in new coverage by Giovanni
Dela-Rosa, an analyst at Deutsche Bank AG. The brokerage has a
12-month share-price estimate of 3.80 pesos.  “The company has assembled an enviable portfolio of
infrastructure assets that is cash generative, solid and hard to
replicate,” Dela-Rosa wrote in a Feb. 10 note. The stock fell
3.1 percent to 3.48 pesos.    SM Development Corp . (SMDC PM): The property company owned
by the country’s richest man, Henry Sy, said net income
increased 62 percent to 3 billion pesos last year. Real estate
sales increased 73 percent to 9.1 billion pesos, the company
said in a regulatory filing. The stock slid 0.6 percent to 7.20
pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cecilia Yap in Manila at   cyap19@bloomberg.net 
